6
00:00:11,880 --> 00:00:13,380
I will wait for you at the canteen.

7
00:00:13,490 --> 00:00:14,460
I won’t go.

8
00:00:16,059 --> 00:00:18,070
You have a heart of stone.

9
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:19,990
I’ve been following you
for almost a month already.

10
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:22,080
I’m not asking you to do it.

11
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,880
Anyway, I will get lunch for you.

12
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,000
Why are you so stubborn?

13
00:00:28,610 --> 00:00:31,410
I will wait until you come.

14
00:00:31,610 --> 00:00:32,290
Okay?

15
00:00:32,380 --> 00:00:34,370
See you later. Bye bye.

16
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:35,840
In!

17
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:24,880
It’s late already.

18
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:27,920
Maybe he went home already.

19
00:02:00,390 --> 00:02:01,570
In.

20
00:02:07,990 --> 00:02:09,990
You finally came.

21
00:02:16,990 --> 00:02:17,990
In.

22
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:23,290
[Dean.]

23
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:25,470
[Dean.]

24
00:02:26,050 --> 00:02:27,060
Dean!

25
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,890
What’s wrong with you?

26
00:02:30,070 --> 00:02:32,079
You didn’t respond
when I called your name.

27
00:02:33,490 --> 00:02:34,490
Nothing.

28
00:02:34,829 --> 00:02:35,510
I…

29
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,600
I just feel like I’ve forgotten something.

30
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:38,990
But,

31
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:41,340
you just said “In”.

32
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:42,880
What was that about?

33
00:02:47,490 --> 00:02:47,990
Whatever.

34
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:49,490
Let’s go.

35
00:02:49,490 --> 00:02:50,990
We should go to class now.

36
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:52,940
[Until We Meet Again]

37
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:57,170
Team and Pharm,
what do you guys want for lunch?

38
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,330
No, thanks.

39
00:04:58,990 --> 00:05:00,600
We'll go buy some food then.

40
00:05:00,690 --> 00:05:01,590
Okay.

41
00:05:01,690 --> 00:05:03,320
If you want anything, just catch up!

42
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:04,790
-Okay.
-Be right back.

43
00:05:05,350 --> 00:05:06,650
I’ll be right back.

44
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:14,270
Manaow and Del seem so close.

45
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:18,600
Of course, they practice
the play together every day.

46
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:20,290
Right. That’s true.

47
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:22,290
What were you thinking?

48
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:26,010
Where is everyone?

49
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:30,320
Who invited you to join us?

50
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:32,490
I’m a grown-up.

51
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:34,570
I can invite myself.

52
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,840
Get up. Go sit over there.

53
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:39,870
The owner of this seat is here.

54
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,650
I will let you win this time.

55
00:05:46,830 --> 00:05:48,820
You’re so nosy.

56
00:05:59,990 --> 00:06:01,880
The breakfast this morning

57
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,100
was so good.

58
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,490
You know,

59
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,990
he’s so stingy.

60
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,570
He wouldn’t let me have a bite.

61
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:14,360
I feel so sorry for you.

62
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,090
Because you’re not Dean,

63
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:18,490
Pharm doesn’t care about you.

64
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,130
Pharm…

65
00:06:21,210 --> 00:06:22,210
Team.

66
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,320
Don’t listen to Team.

67
00:06:25,490 --> 00:06:27,290
He’s always talking nonsense.

68
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:29,390
Are you shy?

69
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:30,490
Don’t be shy.

70
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:31,870
You’re blushing now.

71
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:33,290
That's enough.

72
00:06:33,370 --> 00:06:34,659
You’re being extra now.

73
00:06:34,780 --> 00:06:35,990
Let’s go buy food.

74
00:06:35,990 --> 00:06:36,810
I’m hungry.

75
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:37,490
No!

76
00:06:37,490 --> 00:06:38,990
Let’s go buy food. I’m hungry!

77
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:40,490
I’m not going with you.

78
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,060
What are you eating?

79
00:06:54,409 --> 00:06:55,409
Spicy chicken.

80
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,400
Is it delicious?

81
00:06:56,950 --> 00:06:58,730
Delicious, just like how you made it.

82
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,810
I will make it for you next time.

83
00:07:00,890 --> 00:07:01,890
Looking forward to it.

84
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:02,830
Okay.

85
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:08,430
Dude, what the hell!

86
00:07:34,990 --> 00:07:35,950
Pharm.

87
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,300
Huh?

88
00:07:37,659 --> 00:07:38,860
What's wrong?

89
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,240
Nothing.

90
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:42,500
Are you sure?

91
00:07:43,710 --> 00:07:45,000
Pharm.

92
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:46,790
Are you okay?

93
00:07:46,990 --> 00:07:48,490
Are you sick?

94
00:07:48,690 --> 00:07:50,490
Your face is so red.

95
00:07:51,490 --> 00:07:52,620
I’m okay.

96
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:56,490
Try breathing out.

97
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:00,490
Like this.

98
00:08:04,990 --> 00:08:05,990
That seems normal.

99
00:08:05,990 --> 00:08:06,990
What are you trying to do?

100
00:08:06,990 --> 00:08:08,490
His face is so red.

101
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:10,130
That’s true.

102
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,050
It really is.

103
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,000
Let us know if you’re not okay.

104
00:08:20,990 --> 00:08:21,990
Del,

105
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:24,200
have you seen this?

106
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:25,290
I noticed you like make-up.

107
00:08:26,820 --> 00:08:28,820
I bought it the day it was released.

108
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,990
Really?

109
00:08:31,490 --> 00:08:32,289
Oh, right.

110
00:08:32,390 --> 00:08:34,580
What are you guys doing
for the Open House event?

111
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,429
There will be some stands at my faculty.

112
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:39,490
There’s a walking tour to look around.

113
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,289
For the swimming club, we're going to

114
00:08:42,370 --> 00:08:45,380
introduce our activities and do
a dunk tank water game.

115
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,310
I have to help my faculty in the morning.

116
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:50,010
I will help you later in the afternoon.

117
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:53,450
Okay. I already told
the teacher about that.

118
00:08:56,050 --> 00:08:58,040
Swimming club seniors are so mean.

119
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,130
They let all the freshers
become the dunk tank boy.

120
00:09:04,390 --> 00:09:07,990
I will definitely find time
to play the game.

121
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:10,710
Manaow.

122
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:12,490
Calm down.

123
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:16,390
Faculty of Arts is going to organize
some activities and games.

124
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:19,490
Also, the drama club will perform
a short stage play.

125
00:09:20,110 --> 00:09:21,260
Pharm, how about you?

126
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,900
My faculty will have
an educational guidance,

127
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:26,490
board decorations

128
00:09:26,580 --> 00:09:28,190
and games with desserts as reward.

129
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:30,080
The person who will make desserts is…

130
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,840
Pharm, of course.

131
00:09:35,490 --> 00:09:37,490
It’s very obvious whose idea this is.

132
00:09:37,990 --> 00:09:39,690
It’s Team’s idea.

133
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:43,070
He told our faculty members to hire
the cooking club to make desserts.

134
00:09:43,110 --> 00:09:46,380
Actually, the cooking club
will not have any stands.

135
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,310
I just want to eat.

136
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:55,990
Pharm, do you know what desserts
you're going to make?

137
00:09:56,990 --> 00:09:59,770
The club members are planning
to make Bulan Dan Mek.

138
00:09:59,850 --> 00:10:01,860
Not much people know about this dessert.

139
00:10:01,990 --> 00:10:03,990
We are planning to make
two types of dessert.

140
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:06,490
But we aren’t sure
what we are going to make yet.

141
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:08,530
How about Look Choup?

142
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,830
It has to be star-shaped too.

143
00:10:19,990 --> 00:10:20,990
Dean,

144
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,590
what dessert should he make?

145
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:26,400
I think...

146
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,860
How about Luem Kleun?

147
00:10:32,990 --> 00:10:33,990
Right.

148
00:10:35,490 --> 00:10:36,490
Dean.

149
00:10:38,970 --> 00:10:39,970
I’m suddenly full.

150
00:10:42,490 --> 00:10:44,490
I want to eat Luem Kleun already.

151
00:10:50,490 --> 00:10:51,980
Don’t forget to eat your lunch.

152
00:10:52,990 --> 00:10:54,990
Don’t forget to swallow it too.

153
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,050
Be careful not to choke.

154
00:10:58,230 --> 00:10:59,620
Tell that to yourself.

155
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:19,450
[Good night, Dean.]

156
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:49,020
I just want to make something nice
for you to eat.

157
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:06,850
Here it is.

158
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,830
The best instant noodle in the world!

159
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:25,190
You can’t even make proper instant noodle?

160
00:12:28,690 --> 00:12:30,690
I’ll make it myself next time.

161
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:36,680
I just want to make something nice
for you to eat.

162
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,690
By the way,

163
00:12:51,990 --> 00:12:55,690
are you starting to like me now?

164
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:59,720
How come you still don’t know.

165
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:03,810
I just want to hear you say it.

166
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,230
Just keep guessing then.

167
00:13:08,980 --> 00:13:10,970
You’re so mean.

168
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:15,590
I do like you.

169
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,190
I'll go make a new one.

170
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:20,780
What did you just say?

171
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:23,860
What did you just say?

172
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:10,500
Dean.

173
00:14:11,610 --> 00:14:12,540
Dean.

174
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:15,470
Dean!

175
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:17,910
Dean!

176
00:14:20,290 --> 00:14:21,500
Open the door.

177
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:22,600
Dean!

178
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:27,000
Open the door, please.

179
00:14:32,770 --> 00:14:34,000
You scared me.

180
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Are you okay?

181
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:37,520
I'm fine.

182
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:44,890
I’m fine.

183
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:46,890
I’ve got a headache.

184
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:50,780
Should we go to the hospital?

185
00:14:54,690 --> 00:14:55,690
No need.

186
00:14:58,740 --> 00:14:59,740
I’m okay.

187
00:15:01,790 --> 00:15:03,290
Are you really okay?

188
00:15:06,430 --> 00:15:07,690
I’m okay.

189
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,920
Don’t tell our parents about this.

190
00:15:14,010 --> 00:15:16,000
I just dozed off.

191
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:53,050
Dean,

192
00:15:54,030 --> 00:15:56,040
are you really okay?

193
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,650
I’m just tired.

194
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,500
Thank you.

195
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,030
[Faculty of Economics]

196
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,420
[Courses, clubs and activities]

197
00:16:36,690 --> 00:16:39,190
This way!
You won’t be disappointed.

198
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:41,270
Come to this faculty.

199
00:16:46,690 --> 00:16:48,470
Is this Thai coconut milk custard?

200
00:16:48,570 --> 00:16:51,410
But the colour is so different
from the ones I’ve seen before.

201
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,190
This is Bulan Dan Mek.

202
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,780
Do you know it?

203
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,590
It is a traditional Thai dessert.

204
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:59,690
The middle part is made from egg.

205
00:16:59,700 --> 00:17:01,370
Bulan means moon.

206
00:17:01,450 --> 00:17:03,880
Its meaning refers
to the moon in the night sky.

207
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:05,599
You can try it.

208
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:19,540
Thank you.

209
00:17:26,470 --> 00:17:29,470
It’s so delicious. Where can I buy it?

210
00:17:30,130 --> 00:17:32,190
It tastes like coconut milk custard.

211
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:33,240
It smells so nice.

212
00:17:34,690 --> 00:17:36,690
The texture is similar
to Thai floral rice cakes.

213
00:17:36,780 --> 00:17:37,770
It’s very yummy.

214
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:40,190
One piece per person.

215
00:17:40,190 --> 00:17:42,690
If you want more, you can look around
our faculty building

216
00:17:42,690 --> 00:17:44,190
and answer the questions.

217
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:46,690
If you get it right, you will get
a coupon for the dessert.

218
00:17:46,770 --> 00:17:48,350
We also have Kanom Pra Pai.

219
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:50,750
Thank you so much.

220
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:53,690
Pharm, do you want to take a break?

221
00:17:53,780 --> 00:17:56,670
You worked until late last night.
I’ll ask someone else to help.

222
00:17:57,300 --> 00:18:00,190
I will come back
in the late afternoon then.

223
00:18:00,190 --> 00:18:00,870
Sure.

224
00:18:00,870 --> 00:18:02,070
See you later.

225
00:18:20,590 --> 00:18:21,600
I think

226
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:23,150
I need more make-up.

227
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:24,180
More?

228
00:18:24,690 --> 00:18:25,680
I don’t want it to fade.

229
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:29,690
-Want some?
-No, thanks.

230
00:18:29,690 --> 00:18:31,010
I’m good.

231
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:31,880
It's going to fade.

232
00:18:31,970 --> 00:18:32,770
It’s okay.

233
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,820
I don't think your make up will ever fade.

234
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,900
You’re already beautiful.

235
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:44,990
What are you doing here?

236
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,690
What’s that in your hand?

237
00:18:46,780 --> 00:18:47,780
Let’s have a look.

238
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:52,190
Is there anything for me to eat?

239
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:54,250
I’m so nervous.

240
00:18:54,380 --> 00:18:55,380
Me too.

241
00:18:55,460 --> 00:18:58,470
I need your desserts to cheer me up.

242
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:00,130
Here.

243
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:03,690
This is for you guys.

244
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:04,820
For you two to share.

245
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:05,900
Okay.

246
00:19:07,690 --> 00:19:09,690
Do you have one for Team?

247
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:11,190
Here.

248
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:13,830
He will be angry if
I don’t have something for him.

249
00:19:13,910 --> 00:19:14,910
How about…

250
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Dean?

251
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:16,890
This one.

252
00:19:18,890 --> 00:19:19,880
Del!

253
00:19:21,540 --> 00:19:22,540
What are you doing?

254
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:25,690
No!

255
00:19:25,690 --> 00:19:27,220
Delete it.

256
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:27,980
I won’t.

257
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,560
Del…

258
00:19:30,010 --> 00:19:32,000
Dean replied already.

259
00:19:33,690 --> 00:19:34,830
He said,

260
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:37,870
"Find me at the Faculty
of Business Administration."

261
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,930
"I’ll be here until noon."

262
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:42,010
"Please come."

263
00:19:43,510 --> 00:19:44,630
Just go there now!

264
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:45,690
Yeah! Dean is waiting.

265
00:19:45,690 --> 00:19:47,180
Quick!

266
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:48,690
Before the desserts are spoiled!

267
00:19:48,690 --> 00:19:49,490
Right?

268
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:52,990
Why is there none for me?

269
00:19:55,530 --> 00:19:56,530
Del.

270
00:19:59,190 --> 00:20:01,370
There are many left at my faculty.

271
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:04,650
I don’t want to go there.

272
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:07,290
I won’t see you there if I go now.

273
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:12,590
By the way,

274
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:14,930
have you been thinking about what I asked?

275
00:20:17,270 --> 00:20:19,840
I remember that I rejected you already.

276
00:20:21,690 --> 00:20:23,970
I know.
That's why I want to ask you again.

277
00:20:24,010 --> 00:20:25,710
Have you been thinking thoroughly?

278
00:20:28,770 --> 00:20:30,770
Why would I waste my time thinking?

279
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:31,860
Because

280
00:20:32,010 --> 00:20:34,710
I don’t have feelings for you in that way.

281
00:20:41,690 --> 00:20:45,190
Ouch!

282
00:20:58,060 --> 00:21:00,050
You have someone that you like already?

283
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:03,800
Yes.

284
00:21:08,630 --> 00:21:10,140
Is it Dean?

285
00:21:16,190 --> 00:21:17,190
