00:47:17,840 --> 00:47:18,920
I tried on lipsticks.

573
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:20,310
I’ll clean it for her later.

574
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:25,840
What should we eat today?

575
00:47:26,630 --> 00:47:27,620
Anything.

576
00:47:27,710 --> 00:47:28,720
But...

577
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:30,550
not Western Cuisine.

578
00:47:30,640 --> 00:47:32,640
Why are you so picky?

579
00:47:36,750 --> 00:47:38,740
How about Shabu-shabu?

580
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:40,840
That sounds good.

581
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:41,840
I’m in.

582
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,840
Anything is good for me.

583
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,840
Okay.

584
00:47:46,340 --> 00:47:47,340
Let’s go.

585
00:47:56,010 --> 00:47:57,410
What?

586
00:47:57,560 --> 00:47:58,750
Don’t even think about it.

587
00:47:58,840 --> 00:48:01,340
Go away. Start walking.

588
00:48:02,460 --> 00:48:04,340
You know me too well.

589
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:09,390
We should interrogate them too.

590
00:48:09,540 --> 00:48:10,840
I need an update.

591
00:48:14,980 --> 00:48:18,340
Do you know that this restaurant
uses organic vegetables?

592
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:21,840
This is good for my diet.

593
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:22,930
You’re on diet?

594
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:24,840
Here I come.

595
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:26,090
Got some veggies.

596
00:48:29,840 --> 00:48:31,840
We won’t get fat eating this.

597
00:48:33,020 --> 00:48:35,020
How was the stage play today?

598
00:48:36,140 --> 00:48:42,250
Today, our play is about a love story.

599
00:48:42,340 --> 00:48:46,340
The main character woke up and found
a red thread tied to his finger.

600
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:49,000
So, he went on a journey
to find the other end of the thread.

601
00:48:49,390 --> 00:48:52,060
What’s the meaning of the red thread?

602
00:48:52,150 --> 00:48:55,470
I will just cut it if I woke up
and had a red thread tied to my finger.

603
00:48:55,550 --> 00:48:56,550
So annoying.

604
00:48:56,630 --> 00:48:59,260
You’re not romantic at all.

605
00:48:59,730 --> 00:49:00,740
Let me explain.

606
00:49:03,150 --> 00:49:04,830
Japanese people believe that

607
00:49:04,930 --> 00:49:09,800
soulmates will have the red thread
tied to their left pinky.

608
00:49:09,830 --> 00:49:12,690
It symbolizes the blood vessel
from the heart,

609
00:49:12,770 --> 00:49:15,560
tying to the person that
you are destined to be with.

610
00:49:18,350 --> 00:49:19,840
Do you understand?

611
00:49:19,920 --> 00:49:20,930
So what?

612
00:49:23,940 --> 00:49:25,950
It’s a belief, you know?

613
00:49:28,840 --> 00:49:29,840
Like this.

614
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:34,340
Team!

615
00:49:36,580 --> 00:49:37,910
I understand that now.

616
00:49:38,840 --> 00:49:40,340
You guys are soulmates.

617
00:49:44,210 --> 00:49:45,720
Just wait until it’s my turn.

618
00:49:45,830 --> 00:49:46,840
Delete it now.

619
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:47,840
No.

620
00:49:47,840 --> 00:49:49,340
Don’t delete it.

621
00:49:49,340 --> 00:49:51,340
When I was practising the stage play,

622
00:49:51,340 --> 00:49:53,840
I also heard the Chinese legend
about the red thread.

623
00:49:55,500 --> 00:49:57,840
What’s the difference?

624
00:49:58,440 --> 00:49:59,340
It’s different.

625
00:49:59,340 --> 00:50:03,340
Japanese people believe that the
red thread is tied to the left pinky.

626
00:50:03,340 --> 00:50:07,640
But, the Chinese legend says that
two people destined to be together,

627
00:50:07,640 --> 00:50:10,830
will have the red thread
tied to their ankles.

628
00:50:12,790 --> 00:50:14,780
Have you heard about this tale?

629
00:50:15,540 --> 00:50:17,450
Lovers who cannot be together,

630
00:50:17,660 --> 00:50:20,840
will tie the red thread
around their wrists.

631
00:50:20,840 --> 00:50:22,840
And commit double suicide.

632
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:30,840
They believe that the red thread
will bring them back together.

633
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:31,830
Korn!

634
00:50:37,560 --> 00:50:38,390
That’s deep.

635
00:50:44,020 --> 00:50:45,530
When they are reborn again,

636
00:50:46,430 --> 00:50:47,520
both of them

637
00:50:48,260 --> 00:50:52,560
will feel like they have known
each other for so long.

638
00:50:52,600 --> 00:50:55,030
Like they've waited for their whole lives.

639
00:50:55,590 --> 00:50:57,040
I got goosebumps already.

640
00:50:58,070 --> 00:51:01,580
I want to know how they feel
when they first meet each other.

641
00:51:04,780 --> 00:51:05,790
They feel…

642
00:51:07,840 --> 00:51:08,840
warm.

643
00:51:11,460 --> 00:51:12,460
Longing.

644
00:51:14,650 --> 00:51:15,650
Overwhelmed.

645
00:51:22,750 --> 00:51:24,740
If we died and we were born again,

646
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:27,440
do you think we will
find each other again?

647
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:29,840
We will.

648
00:51:30,940 --> 00:51:32,930
Really?

649
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:34,600
Yes.

650
00:51:35,330 --> 00:51:37,120
I will keep searching until I find you.

651
00:51:39,640 --> 00:51:42,640
Promise me that we will
always find each other.

652
00:51:51,340 --> 00:51:52,840
Promise.

653
00:52:04,730 --> 00:52:08,390
[Next episode]

654
00:52:05,470 --> 00:52:07,570
Are you saying that
you want to have a kid?

655
00:52:08,840 --> 00:52:12,280
I made this for you. Have you eaten yet?

656
00:52:12,340 --> 00:52:13,340
Not yet.

657
00:52:14,040 --> 00:52:16,190
Why don’t you come and join us?

658
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:17,160
Are you sure?

659
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:19,840
This is the spare key to my room.

660
00:52:20,810 --> 00:52:22,410
Please keep it safe.
